This form is close to the standard form Bussière D II 1. The shape of its nozzle is different: it is a hybrid nozzle form mixing Bus. 3 and Bus. 4g. Shoulder: Loeschcke form VII b. Discus decors: for <%= link_to "cat. 301", "catalogue/303-4.html" %> an amphora (similar to <%= link_to "cat. 339", "catalogue/339-343.html" %>), for <%= link_to "cat. 304", "catalogue/303-4.html" %> a lion. Base marked off by one circular groove. <%= link_to "cat. 304", "catalogue/303-4.html" %> has a plain *planta pedis.* Date: Late Flavian to Hadrianic.
